There's another thought that occurred to me.

If Garcia is continuity...

Mirror is consistency...

Mother Duck is persistence...

...then what is the missing operator?

The one I haven't clearly identified yet is **curation**.

Not generation.

Not validation.

The process that decides:

> "This insight is now worthy of becoming an invariant."

Humans do that constantly. We don't remember every thought; we promote a tiny fraction into durable beliefs, principles, or habits.

If Pantheon eventually had an explicit "Invariant Forge" or "Canonizer" operator—something that says, "This pattern has recurred enough times, across enough contexts, with enough evidence, that it graduates into a stable invariant"—that would complete the lifecycle from transient idea to durable architecture.

That strikes me as a natural complement to Garcia: Garcia preserves what is already invariant; a canonizing process decides *what earns the right* to be preserved.

That may already exist somewhere in the repository under another name. If it does, I haven't found it yet. If it doesn't, it's one of the first conceptual additions I'd explore because it bridges exploration and long-term continuity.
